    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "ae826414_68f94078",
        "filename": "lucicfg/testdata/notifiable/tree_closer.star",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 99,
      "author": {
        "id": 1002539
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-02-20T01:00:32Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "TBH I very much don\u0027t like luci-notify config format, it has too many degrees of freedom. I added tree_closers in analogy to how notifications\u003c...\u003e are defined (i.e. there\u0027s a top level entry per builder, and it specifies all things that \"react\" to this builder). \n\nAn alternative would be to create a top level entry per tree closer, and specify inside of it all builders it watches. Would you prefer that instead of the current approach?",
